Sec. 15. Be it further enacted, That the Mayor and City Council shall have power to lay a reasonable tax on all persons and property, both real and personal in said city: Provided, That said tax is to be levied at the beginning of each year, and to be assessed and collected by the officers appointed for that purpose;
Laws of the Republic of Texas.and shall also, he empowered to lay a tax on all taverns and houses of public entertainment, tippling houses, billiard tables, and nine-
pin-alleys and merchants, retail or wholesale.
